column13: 1. I am knowledgeable of the various types and varieties of communication technologies used in healthcare settings (i.e. Electronic Health Record, patient portal, etc. ).
column14: 2. I understand the central role nursing has to plan and implement Health Information Technologies (HIT).
column15: 3. I am able to select and apply the best evidence and practices to deliver care using the available information technologies.
column16: 4. I understand the impact of health information technology (information and communication technologies) on my daily work (workflow processes) and patient/client outcomes.
column17: 5. I am knowledgeable about using health information technology  (information and communication technology to gather data, create information, and generate knowledge) to document care, create a plan of care, and identify trends.
column18: 6. I understand the importance of entering accurate data when documenting care on the patient and how this impacts public and population health.
column19: 7. I am knowledgeable about how data moves from the patient to the enterprise and beyond to public and population health efforts.
column20: 8. I can identify appropriate data to use in planning patient, community, and population care.
column21: 9. I can describe how standardized data is used as a foundation for evidence-based practice.
column22: 10. I can generate information and knowledge from the data contained in health information technology and other databases.
column23: 11. I can use standardized data to evaluate decision-making and outcomes of care.
column24: 12.  I can find and Interpret primary and secondary data to support patient care  (Primary sources provide raw information and first-hand evidence. Secondary sources interpret, analyze or summarize primary sources).
column25: 13. I can use appropriate information and communication technologies in various healthcare settings.
column26: 14. I understand how decision support tools work and how they impact clinical judgment and safe care.
column27: 15. I can identify emerging technologies and know how they impact care outcomes.
column28: 16. I know how to identify the impact of information and communication technology on quality and safe care (i.e. Clinical Decision Support to alert staff to turn patients).
column29: 17. I am competent in using health information technologies to address patientsâ€™ needs and care gaps.
column30: 18. I am knowledgeable about how to plan for and address the unexpected consequences of health information technologies and communication technology implementation.
column31: 19. I understand how data is exchanged both inside and outside of a system to integrate care.
column32: 20. Beyond HIPAA, I understand the latest legal and regulatory requirements that impact the use of health information technology.
column33: 21. I am familiar with a patients right to access, review, and correct their personal health information.
